  • Constructor Details

    • Vacuum

      public Vacuum​(int row, int column, int maxCapacity) throws VacuumException, SpriteException
      Constructor.
      Parameters:
      row - Index of the row in which the vacuum cleaner is initially.
      column - Index of the column in which the vacuum cleaner is initially.
      maxCapacity - Maximum capacity of dirt that the vacuum cleaner can store.
      Throws:
      VacuumException - When the value for the vacuum cleaner's maximum capacity is zero or negative; when the value for the vacuum cleaner's current capacity is negative or higher than the maximum capacity.
      SpriteException - When the index of either the row or the column is incorrect.
